When it comes to laptop brands, there are very few that can compare with the reputation of Lenovo. Lenovo’s laptops have a reputation for reliability, efficiency and performance, all packaged into a sturdy frame. As such a reputable brand, Lenovo prides itself on using the best possible components – such as the impressive 2nd generation AMD Ryzen Pro processors used in the ThinkPad X395. AMD’s 2nd generation AMD Ryzen Pro processors offer incredible performance to business users. Sporting 4 cores and 8 threads, these processors are capable of taking on whatever tasks you place in front of them. With a TDP of up to 15W, they also offer phenomenal power efficiency – making them perfect for laptops such as the ThinkPad X395, which is tailor-made for the businessman who is constantly on the move. The flagship Ryzen 7 Pro can boost its clock frequency up to 4.0GHz – making it an absolute powerhouse. The ThinkPad X395 supports up to the AMD Ryzen 7 Pro processor and combines it with an integrated Vega 10 GPU to give you impressive performance across a wide range of tasks. This is supported by up to 16GB of RAM – a generous amount of memory that will support high-performance tasks such as video editing. Your storage needs are catered to as well, with the X395 offering an impressive 1TB PCIe SSD storage, as well as an additional 256GB of SATA SSD storage. This SSD storage is both sizable and incredibly speedy – with 1TB of PCIe SSD storage being an attractive luxury that will make daily tasks a breeze. All of this is packaged into a compact form factor, with a display size of 13.3-inches being the perfect balance between portability and usability. The ThinkPad X395 also offers up to 14.5 hours of battery life thanks to its impressive 48Whr battery – further proving that this is a device that is well-suited to the on-the-go user. You can also utilise RapidCharge technology which enables you to charge your device from 0% to 80% in just 60 minutes. The ThinkPad X395 is proof that dynamite comes in small packages and should be a major consideration if you’re looking to buy a new business laptop. It’s latest-generation AMD processor, combined with a variety of other impressive specifications, make it one of the best business laptops on the market. Learn more about the ThinkPad X395 here. The specifications of the Lenovo ThinkPad X395 are below. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-316769" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lenovo-x395-1.png" alt="lenovo x395 1" width="640" height="431" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lenovo-x395-1.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lenovo-x395-1-300x202.png 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lenovo-x395-1-594x400.png 594w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lenovo-x395-1-639x430.png 639w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-316773" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lenovo-x395-2.png" alt="lenovo x395 2" width="640" height="431" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lenovo-x395-2.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lenovo-x395-2-300x202.png 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lenovo-x395-2-594x400.png 594w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lenovo-x395-2-639x430.png 639w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-316767" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lenovo-x395-3.png" alt="lenovo x395 3" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/lenovo-x395-3.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uplo